The United States and the Republic of Korea have reaffirmed their commitment to their alliance and mutual defense. They agree to strengthen their deterrence posture and deepen cooperation in areas such as cyber and space. Both countries emphasize the complete denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and intend to address North Korea's nuclear and ballistic missile programs. They also express support for diplomacy and dialogue to achieve this goal and improve human rights in North Korea. The alliance extends beyond the Korean Peninsula and includes cooperation in the Indo-Pacific region, supporting democratic norms, human rights, and the rules-based international order. They pledge to maintain peace and stability, oppose activities that threaten the international order, and promote human rights and the rule of law. The two countries also commit to working together on climate change, global health, emerging technologies, trade, and development. They will strengthen their partnership on critical and emerging technologies, including 5G and 6G, and collaborate on clean energy and space exploration. Additionally, they emphasize the importance of people-to-people ties and promoting democratic values and human rights.